caption: When you think of an ideal Brooklyn slice - Gino's pizza is it. A place full of Italians watching old soccer games, serving up hot Italian comfort food and great, quality pizza. Additionally - when compared with other pizza places in the area, Gino's is INSANELY cheap, cost-wise.  So you've got quality - check You won't break the bank - check Unassuming gem in a great location - check  These types of pizza places are less restaurants, and more of neighborhood institutions. 5/5

Great spot for quality italian food. Got there near six, it wasn't packed at all. The service was friendly and sociable. The place has a cool atmosphere. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I loved.

I have lived on the same block as Gino's for probably 9-10 years and they are one to impress. They always give you warm pizza, and they have the best service. My mother was reading the reviews to other pizza places and said, "I don't need to go anywhere fancy, I can just go up the block to the best Pizza place ever!"

I had my first NY slice here after a hockey game a few blocks away.   The day was March 3,2020.  The slice was excellent and the restaurant was clean.   The bathroom was clean and stocked.   I had to wipe the table but that was ok.   I thank them for the service provided.    They kept me safe just a few weeks before the tragedy.

Please DON'T ever use your credit card here. My family has been going to this pizzeria for 2 years now. My mom made a new debit card and used it strictly for direct deposit from her job, and to pay the phone bill. Nothing else. We used the card here one time, and they spent 15 minutes passing it around from employee to employee. I saw one of them writing something down on a paper while looking at the card, but I gave them the benefit of the doubt. I we just noticed a bunch of purchases made online from her card. We had to report the fraud. It started later in the week from the pizza purchase. If you choose to come here, just pay cash. I am disappointed.
